problem:
There are two possible triangles with $AB = 20,$ $BC = 19,$ and $A = 34^\circ.$  One of them is shown below.  What is the sum of the two possible values of $\angle B,$ in degrees?

[asy]
unitsize (1 cm);

pair A, B, C;

A = (0,0);
B = 5*dir(34);
C = (5,0);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, N);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$20$", (A + B)/2, NW);
label("$19$", (B + C)/2, NE);
label("$34^\circ$", (1,0.4));
[/asy]
